ivardefs.name: approvalDate
ivardefs.desc: The date on which the resource content was approved by the publisher. Approval happens once when the content is officially approved for usage.

ivardefs.name: contact_
ivardefs.desc: Contact details to assist a user in finding and communicating with the publisher.

ivardefs.name: contributor_
ivardefs.desc: A contributor to the content of the module, including authors, editors, reviewers, and endorsers.

ivardefs.name: copyright
ivardefs.desc: A copyright statement relating to the service definition and/or its contents. Copyright statements are generally legal restrictions on the use and publishing of the service definition.

ivardefs.name: dataRequirement_
ivardefs.desc: Data requirements are a machine processable description of the data required by the module in order to perform a successful evaluation.

ivardefs.name: date
ivardefs.desc: The date  (and optionally time) when the service definition was published. The date must change if and when the business version changes and it must change if the status code changes. In addition, it should change when the substantive content of the servi

ivardefs.name: description
ivardefs.desc: A free text natural language description of the service definition from a consumer's perspective.

ivardefs.name: effectivePeriod
ivardefs.desc: The period during which the service definition content was or is planned to be in active use.

ivardefs.name: experimental
ivardefs.desc: A boolean value to indicate that this service definition is authored for testing purposes (or education/evaluation/marketing), and is not intended to be used for genuine usage.

ivardefs.name: identifier_
ivardefs.desc: A formal identifier that is used to identify this service definition when it is represented in other formats, or referenced in a specification, model, design or an instance. This is used for CMS or NQF identifiers for a measure artifact. Note that at leas

ivardefs.name: jurisdiction_
ivardefs.desc: A legal or geographic region in which the service definition is intended to be used.

ivardefs.name: lastReviewDate
ivardefs.desc: The date on which the resource content was last reviewed. Review happens periodically after approval, but doesn't change the original approval date.

ivardefs.name: name
ivardefs.desc: A natural language name identifying the service definition. This name should be usable as an identifier for the module by machine processing applications such as code generation.

ivardefs.name: operationDefinition
ivardefs.desc: A reference to the operation that is used to invoke this service.

ivardefs.name: publisher
ivardefs.desc: The name of the individual or organization that published the service definition.

ivardefs.name: purpose
ivardefs.desc: Explaination of why this service definition is needed and why it has been designed as it has.

ivardefs.name: relatedArtifact_
ivardefs.desc: Related resources such as additional documentation, justification, or bibliographic references.

ivardefs.name: status
ivardefs.desc: The status of this service definition. Enables tracking the life-cycle of the content.

ivardefs.name: title
ivardefs.desc: A short, descriptive, user-friendly title for the service definition.

ivardefs.name: topic_
ivardefs.desc: Descriptive topics related to the module. Topics provide a high-level categorization of the module that can be useful for filtering and searching.

ivardefs.name: trigger_
ivardefs.desc: The trigger element defines when the rule should be invoked. This information is used by consumers of the rule to determine how to integrate the rule into a specific workflow.

ivardefs.name: url
ivardefs.desc: An absolute URI that is used to identify this service definition when it is referenced in a specification, model, design or an instance. This SHALL be a URL, SHOULD be globally unique, and SHOULD be an address at which this service definition is (or will

ivardefs.name: usage
ivardefs.desc: A detailed description of how the module is used from a clinical perspective.

ivardefs.name: useContext_
ivardefs.desc: The content was developed with a focus and intent of supporting the contexts that are listed. These terms may be used to assist with indexing and searching for appropriate service definition instances.

ivardefs.name: version
ivardefs.desc: The identifier that is used to identify this version of the service definition when it is referenced in a specification, model, design or instance. This is an arbitrary value managed by the service definition author and is not expected to be globally uniq
